items.title: IMPORTANT!
items.content: On each trial, you will have 30 seconds to respond. After this 30 seconds, if you have not responded then the trial will end and you will immediately be moved on to the next trial.
When you are ready, click "continue" to begin.

items.title: Hello, and welcome!
items.content:
You will now complete a test that is used to measure how well people can relate concepts in different ways.
You will be presented with 67 total trials in this task. On each trial, you will see 1-3 statements about the relationship between imaginary words (for example: CUG is the same as JOM, JOM is the same as VEK). You will also be presented with a question on the bottom of the screen asking about the relationship between these words (for example: is CUG different to VEK?).

Your task is to answer this question accurately, by selecting either "YES" or "NO", based on the information that is given to you.
If you are using a smartphone, you can select yes or no by simply tapping on the yes/no buttons. If you are using a computer, then simply click the yes/no buttons.
